# Subagent Report Verification Protocol

Never mark a task complete from the report alone. Always run independent verification.

## Verification by Task Type

### File Creation / Secret Initialization
```powershell
# Check no placeholder values remain
Select-String "your_|changeme|placeholder|secret_here|xxx" <file>
# Must return nothing
```
Read the actual file. Do not trust "I set the value" without reading the content yourself.

### Docker Services Started
```powershell
docker-compose ps
# Every service must show "Up" or "running"
# Any showing "Exit" or "Restarting" → read logs:
docker-compose logs --tail=50 <failed_service>
```

### Scripts Executed (DB init, seed, migrations)
```bash
# Query the database directly — don't trust the script output summary
# See verification-scripts.md in the global skill for the query pattern
```
Always check actual row counts or table existence, not just whether the script ran.

### API / Health Verification
```powershell
# Re-run the actual HTTP call yourself — don't trust the report's summary
Invoke-RestMethod -Uri "http://localhost:<PORT>/health" -Method Get
```

## Subagent Prompt Requirement

Always include this in prompts for infrastructure or deployment tasks:

> "If you encounter errors during any step, diagnose and fix them autonomously — do not pause to ask for permission. Document every fix in your report's Issues section. Only set `status: COMPLETE` if you independently verified the result by running the actual command or reading the actual file."

This prevents two failure modes:
- The "Should I proceed?" halt (subagent asks for permission mid-task)
- The false-positive report (subagent claims completion without verification)

## Report Status — What They Actually Mean

| Status | What it means in practice | Required action |
|--------|--------------------------|-----------------|
| COMPLETE | Subagent believes it's done | Run independent verification |
| PARTIAL | Something left undone | Read Issues, spawn follow-up |
| BLOCKED | Cannot proceed | Identify blocker, resolve or ask user |

## Model Trust Reference

| Model | Trust level | Verify |
|-------|------------|--------|
| fast | Low | Everything |
| default | Medium | All critical steps |

## Red Flags in a Report

- "Manual check confirmed" with no command output shown
- `Issues: None` on a task with known complexity
- `started` → `completed` timestamp gap too short for the work
- All acceptance criteria listed but none have actual output/evidence
